# Compliance Agent — Cursor Rules

## LLM stack
- Primary chat LLM: `claude-sonnet-4-20250514` via anthropic SDK
- Fallback 1: OpenAI GPT-4o
- Fallback 2: rule-based engine (no API key required)

## Architecture rules
- `pages/` files: UI only — import from `core/` and `db/`, zero business logic
- `core/` never imports streamlit
- All DB access via `db/client.py` only
- All LLM calls via `core/llm/client.py` only
- Config via Pydantic Settings in `config.py`, not direct `os.getenv()` calls
- Pydantic v2 models for all DB entities
- No `eval()` — use `json.loads()`
- Use `deduplicate_sources()` from `core/rag/utils.py`
- Jurisdiction names are DB-driven, never hardcoded in logic
- Jurisdiction resolution: always use `jurisdiction_id` (int), never raw string

## Naming conventions
- DB operations: `get_*`, `create_*`, `update_*`, `delete_*`
- UI functions: `show_*`
- Pydantic models: PascalCase

## Testing
- Every core module requires corresponding tests
- Use mock/fake DB clients, not real Supabase
- No real API calls in tests

## Legal
- Legal disclaimer appended to every compliance result
- Rule-based fallback always works without any API key
